For the second time in four months, President Muhammadu Buhari will be going to London, the United Kingdom for another round of medical checks. He will leave Abuja today for the scheduled medical follow-up.
According to a statement yesterday by presidential spokesman, Mr. Femi Adesina, the president is due back in the country in the second week of July. Earlier in the year, the president went to the UK to see his doctors, leaving on March 30 and returned on April 16.